situations from a variety of perspectives. Feldman explores their personal experiences and daily work in order to crack open wider issues about sovereignty, action, ethics, and, ultimately, being human. Situated at the intersection of the EU migration apparatus and the global, clandestine networks it identifies as security threats, this book allows Feldman to outline an ethnographically-based theory of sovereign action.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aHuman smugglingzEuropean Union countriesxPrevention. 0aHuman traffickingzEuropean Union countriesxPrevention. 0aPolice ethicszEuropean Union countries. 0aSovereigntyxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aUndercover operationsxMoral and ethical aspectszEuropean Union countries. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aEuropean Union.  aSovereignty.  aaction.  amigration.  apersonhood.  apolice.  asecurity.  astate of exception.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360766840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503607668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503607668.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles